brewery.brewery_name: Bières de Chimay (Abbaye Notre Dame de Scourmont)

items.badge_description: It's New Brew Thursday! Drink a new beer on three Thursdays in a 30 day period! Need help finding a new beer? Check out the latest episode of New Brew Thursday today!

brewery.brewery_name: Bières de Chimay (Abbaye Notre Dame de Scourmont)

beer.beer_description: A traditional Belgian-style farmhouse ale, the perfect combination of elements came together in their #7 fermenter. You could call it fate, but they called it Tank 7, and so it is. Beginning with a big surge of fruity aromatics and grapefruit-hoppy notes, the flavor of this complex, straw-colored ale tapers off to a peppery, dry finish.

Dark Smooth Stout.
Established in 2009 this young brewery is already producing award winning ales. Monty's Midnight is a lovely smooth, rich stout, full of dark fruit flavours.

Monty's Brewery is in powys, Mid-Wales, close to the historic town of Montgomery.

To read more find us on the web www.montysbrewery.co.uk

Ingredients: Water, Malted Barley, Wheat, Hops and Yeast
Allergens: contains Gluten
